### Bug
It is possible to find a path that does not lead to the goal state. This is known as a **backtrack**.

![Buggy Algorithm](https://docs.google.com/drawings/d/1FqNhxZnx8F53D0QqLQX0_0uU_mCbQZ0Xwz-Fj742h7g/pub?w=842&h=600)

### Solution
The algorithm has to go through the following steps:
- Add the initial node to the queue
- If the node matches the goal, then the goal node has been reached and the algorithm is finished
- If the node does not match the goal, then add each of its successors to the queue
- Continue this process until the queue is empty

The algorithm is finished when the queue is empty, so the algorithm does not traverse the graph more than once.

